Posting this in here as well as <#CJ5DN6RKP|email-development> because it is HubL related :sweat_smile:

Hello! I am looking to better understand what might be going wrong with the module I have created for line-items being inserted into a programmable email.

I have this code that works wonders:
```{% set line_items = deal['line_items'] %}

&lt;ul&gt;
  {% for line_item in line_items %}
    &lt;li&gt;
      &lt;h4&gt;{{ line_item['name'] }}&lt;/h4&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Quantity: {{ line_item['quantity'] }}&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Price: {{ line_item['price'] }}&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
  {% endfor %}
&lt;/ul&gt;```
But when I try to add something that will multiply the quantity by the price in order to get the _total_ it makes the template in-usable. I was using something like this:
```&lt;p&gt;Total: ${{ line_item['quantity'] * line_item['price'] }}&lt;/p&gt;```
However this seems to be the issue. Any time I try to get the module to do math on the values.
